\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13255613\charrsid484402 Has written four or five earlier autobiographical documents.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid10294204\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13255613\charrsid484402 Born 4 April 1946, Palmer\rquote s Green, North London. Parents aspirational working class. Mother from Durham mining family; grandfather institutionalised. Father from Tottenham}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402  (a barber)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13255613\charrsid484402 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid15600129\charrsid484402 (Mother worked in factories, laundries etc 
\endash  see below) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13255613\charrsid484402 Both parents kind, caring. With father, talked
 about little. When Ken came out in 1966, father did meet Everard and have a meal with him. Father keen for Ken and older brother to go to university, which both did \endash 
 brother to Hull, biology. Nobody in family had gone before. Encouraged to do homework. But Ken\rquote s A levels poor, A for literature, D for economics and fail for French, so started instead in college.
\par At junior school, influence of Miss Ford \endash  classical music, debates. Sports teacher Rennie married he music teacher. Passed 11 plus and went to Glendale Grammar School, as brother. While there it became comprehensive.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f42\insrsid2695404\charrsid484402  Became a stuck up little grammar school boy! Loved musicals, at junior school wanted to be a tap dancer, had to drop that. Liked French teacher Tarling and German teacher Moorfield. Ha
d a nervous stutter, sent to therapist. Became school magazine editor (later edited }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid2695404\charrsid484402 Sociological Life }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid2695404\charrsid484402 
in Essex Department). And became head boy. School a new amalgamation with smart new building. Not into sport at all, just watched. Organised dances.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13255613\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid2695404\charrsid484402 Sixth Form all good teachers. Len Hadley economics, wise, encouraged him to apply for social sciences.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid10241803\charrsid484402 
 History teacher also theatre teacher. For Carey English teacher, Ken worked hard, started buying more advanced books, etc. But antagonistic relationship - bec
ause Ken at this time a active Christian, churchgoing C of E. Then aged 11/12/14/15 switched to Methodist for Youth Club, became abstainer, ran total abstinence stalls for 4/5 years.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid3478255\charrsid484402 
 Enjoyed dancing, music, girls.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13255613\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid3478255\charrsid484402 Always attracted to boys, but most of friends wee girls. Janet, Jean and Margaret at junior school, but after 11 plus drifted apart.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f42\insrsid16454700\charrsid484402  Still close friends with girls at 18 but not even kissing.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid3478255\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid16454700\charrsid484402 Eccentric uncle came to live with them, but not gay. One of brother\rquote s sons is gay.
\par Thought of becoming a solicitor. But went to Enfield College, which became part of Middlesex Polytechnic, was up and coming. Took External Sociology BA}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402  (1964-7)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid16454700\charrsid484402 . Admitted by Joseph Abraham. But new staff included Stan Cohen, Jock Young, Roy Bailey (now folk singer), Julienne Ford \endash 
like an outpost of LSE. Did economics, statistics, sociology. Second Year Structure of Modern Britain, Comparative Sociology, Social Psychology taught by Stan Cohen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid9786046\charrsid484402 
. Third year, he taught Criminology, which was a turning point. Encouraged essay on homosexuality.. Got 2: 1, rare in those days.
\par Stan \lquote one of the most important people in my life\rquote . Then doing Mods and Rockers. An intellectual at work, also warm and caring. Encouraged him to do Ph D, come to |Durham. But applied to Ph D at LSE \endash  at first rejec
ted by Terence Morris, then accepted by David Downes \endash  because Tessa Blackstone had intervened. Quickly moved from Downes to Paul Rock, \lquote wonderful supervisor\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402 
 (1968-73)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid9786046\charrsid484402 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402 gentle, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid9786046\charrsid484402 important influence.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402  Symbolic interactionist. \endash  ambiguities of life. Darren Thiel his last Ph D. Ken\rquote s thesis became }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402 Sexual Stigma.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid16454700\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402 In vacations, worked in local Youth Employment Office, and on finishing BA, took job in Woking as Youth Employment Officer, Sep 1967 \endash  disliked it, and left after two months.
\par Wrote to Michael Schofield, who had written the only book of the time on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402 Sociological Aspects of Homosexuality}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402  (1966) 
\endash  also researched }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402 The Sexual Behaviour of Young People}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402  (1965).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f42\insrsid15600129\charrsid484402  Went to see him in Hampstead.
\par Social class issue \endash  describes own father\rquote s (barber) and mother\rquote s jobs (factory worker, laundry worker, shop work, home work). How they got to own a house.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid14556789\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid15600129\charrsid484402 Michel Schofield from Leeds, very rich family, posh. But Labour and Civil Rights supporter. \lquote Another world\rquote . But Michael welcoming, made a pass at him. Story of how Michael
 realised gay while a Cambridge student, wrote under pseudonym Gordon Westwood, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid15600129\charrsid484402 The Homosexual in Society}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid15600129\charrsid484402 
 (1951). Involved in Wolfenden Report.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402  Then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402 The Sexual Behaviour of Young People}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402 , followed up with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402 The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402 Sexual Behaviour of Young Adult}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402 s. F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402 or which Ken involved as a Research Officer.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid16454700\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid11538509\charrsid484402 Also met Anthony Grey, director of Homosexual Law Reform Society, became involved, and Albany Trust \endash 
 active in these c 1967 to Gay Liberation Front c 1970. At same time switch social policy to sociology, Downes to Rock.
\par Fieldwork his coming out experience, hanging around gay bars making notes. Describes bars, going down winding stairs to deep cellars. First gay experience, Le Duce Coffee Bar in D\rquote Arblay St, dancing to Motown. A lot of predators around. Public lo
os too risky. Has lost the card box describing the bars. His \lquote immersive fieldwork moment\rquote . Wrote a paper\rquote , \lquote Men in love\rquote .
\par Ten gay couples for project with the Albany Trust. Also in the box. Hopes to deposit some of gay research material at LSE.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid3220241\charrsid484402 Ph D in five years to 1973. Also teaching part time, his first teaching job (from 1968) !968 had been on a full time grant, but lost it because Middlesex gave him a full time teaching post 
\endash  and at the same time, teaching part time at Kingston: which carried on until came to Essex.
\par Self-describes as \lquote workaholic\rquote  and \lquote passionate\rquote .
\par Read John Gagnon and Bill Simon from c 1967, became a great fan, turned Ken onto constructionalism. John was Ken\rquote s Ph D examiner. Describes viva. Had met John earlier through Michael Schofield. John\rquote 
s flamboyant house, and second wife Cathy. Through Michael also met Evelyn Hooker. Became closest to John 1983-4 when he came to England. Got to know Bill through going to Santa Barbara. Both very serious intellectuals. Gave oration for Bill\rquote s fune
ral in Texas, published in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid3220241\charrsid484402 Sexualities}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid6045750\charrsid484402  \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6045750\charrsid484402 
also of John}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid3220241\charrsid484402 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid3220241\charrsid484402 John in 80s, now ill [died 2016]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6045750\charrsid484402 
. Both feel they are now too ignored by researchers. Image of academic generations, falling off the top of the moving staircase. Danger of repeating earlier research if you don\rquote t know what was done.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f42\insrsid3220241\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6045750\charrsid484402 Story of being together at ASA conference, going out for dinner, John would want swishest restaurant, Bill a burger.
\par From Essex got a travel grant to visit US sex research in 1976, Masters and Johns and Kinsey Institute \endash  \lquote inspirational\rquote 
. Also his introduction to American gay life. At Kinsey, masturbation workshops and discussion. Male fashion show. Nude bathing.
\par Kinsey himself did a huge number of interviews. Obsessed. Despite methodological problems, major cultural event. But 
Kinsey had now died ten years earlier, Institute not sure where to go. John ent to Stony Brook, Bill to Houston. Masters and Johnson in St Louis, Washington. Very different, all physiological. No larking around.
\par But incident when nearly arrested in his hotel at end of conference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid2050094 [content removed]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6045750\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4090025\charrsid484402 Importance of National Deviancy Conference for Ken in 970s. Trajectory of research, after Albany Trust project goes off in multiple 
directions. Gay life in London for thesis. Then grant for looking at a range of sexual groups - paedophilia, sadomasochism, transvestism, transgenderism, asexuality, sex workers/prostitution, and sexual dysfunction. With Annabel Faraday. Never published, 
but shaped the rest of his life. Interviews in a box upstairs.
\par Led to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid4090025\charrsid484402 Documents of Life (2)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4090025\charrsid484402 
, which is about problems of life story work. Then 1982 AIDS. Had been hoping to do an ethnography of a sexual health clinic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid1208864\charrsid484402 Annabel did a long interview with a tran
svestite, and other interviews with sex workers, and people seen as sexually dysfunctional. Ken mainly interviewed paedophiles and sadomasochists.  Wrote articles but never published. Discovered variety oof sexual behaviours. Scary case of internal sadoma
sochism. Party where people pouring oil on each other and setting fire. Kink culture. Multiple fetishes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid2050094 [content removed]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid926900\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\ul\insrsid3086790\charrsid484402 Track 2
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid15927977\charrsid484402 All his research is self-reflexive.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid10880635\charrsid484402  Studies homosexuality because is homosexual, AIDS because his friends are dying.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid15927977\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid10880635\charrsid484402 Annabel has been very important to Ken, still in contact. She was heterosexual with boyfriend, becomes lesbian. So does transcriber Janet Parkin. And Linda, wife of visting s
ociologist Harvey Molotch. Harvey also heterosexual becoming gay. [Linda was killed in car crash in Greece.] Annabel became a radical Feminist. Tension between sexual liberation and gender liberation: e.g. over sex workers and prostitution. At this time r
escued by meeting Everard. Annabel criticises notion that lesbian women are like a female version of gay men. Ken and Annabel fell out for ten years. Never able to write a book together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid2050094 [content removed]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid12918984\charrsid484402 
\par Jeffrey Weeks at Essex. Seminars.  Another great inspiration. Got close from 1970 through Gay Liberation Front. Both met their first lovers there.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa200\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11472491 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid12918984\charrsid484402 Mary McIntosh also there. Various
 unpublished papers by her as well as focus article on the homosexual role. Mary was a Parsonian. Then very beautiful, well dressed. Also came to Essex 1975, six months after Ken But she never taught lesbian and gay studies at Essex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402  \endash  instead feminism and socialism}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid12918984\charrsid484402 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 
 Became a good friend, talked a lot.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid12918984\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 Jeffrey Weeks\rquote  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 Coming Out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 
, historical and contemporary. Talks, on marches together.  Distinctive clusters of people who are not mainstream sociology.
\par Ken\rquote s }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 The Making of the Modern Homosexual}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid9502955\charrsid484402  (1981), laying out historical groundwork, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid9502955\charrsid484402 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 s followed by edited volume, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 Modern Homosexualities}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid9502955\charrsid484402  (1992) and Ken wanted a third collective volume on global homosexualities, but he has now published his own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid9502955\charrsid484402 Cosmopolitan Sexualities}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid9502955\charrsid484402 
\par First shock of hearing about AIDS in coffee 
room. Already planning study of a sexual health clinic. Taught a course on sociology of medicine. Went to New York. People dying like flies, horrendous. Wrote some pieces. Then Tony Coxon came to Essex with his AIDS research. Backed out of it, too depress
ing. But galvanised gay movement. Becasme more open to reasonable debate, rather than just shouting and screaming.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid8733169\charrsid484402  While he produced four volume reader on symbolic interactionism.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid13460332\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid8733169\charrsid484402 Difference between theories of symbolic interactionism (evolved through James
, Dewey, Mead, emphasises ever-changing role of experience in life, and the struggle for meaning) and social constructionism (which is narrower, experience of interaction often seen through language \endash 
 Berger and Luckmann). Foucault seminars at Essex.
\par Phases of coming out stories}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6885043\charrsid484402 , discussed in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid6885043\charrsid484402 Sexual Stigma. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f42\insrsid6885043\charrsid484402 Private and public coming out.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid8733169\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6885043\charrsid484402 Queer theory appears late 80s though literature, very American, messing up all our categories and reading for hidden messages. Reinterpreting films. Attraction of innovatory perspective.

\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa200\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid5709978 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\ul\insrsid6885043\charrsid484402 Track 3
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6885043\charrsid484402 Symbolic interactionism as an open theory. Gay Liberation Front made him politically more aware. But has always been politically involved. Interactionism alone is not enough.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4268241\charrsid484402  Who has the power to tell stories? Now less interested in sex as a research topic. Earlier was exciting to be in a new field. Has moved from i
nteractionism towards humanism. Social science should be clear about its values.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid6885043\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4268241\charrsid484402 Danger of post-modernism is its relativism. But not a \lquote realist\rquote  like Ted Benton, it\rquote s much more fragile, emerging truth \endash 
 ultimately unknowable. Every sentence in a life story can be unpacked further and further. Stories different depending on themes.
\par Article on silence and narrative power. When does a story die out? Premarital sex was on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4719515\charrsid484402 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4268241\charrsid484402 e a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4719515\charrsid484402 compelling theme (e.g. Ira Reiss), but now has disappeared. 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\super\insrsid4719515\charrsid484402 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4719515\charrsid484402 
 C hysteria over masturbation. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid4719515\charrsid484402 Telling Sexual Stories.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f42\insrsid4268241\charrsid484402 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid4719515\charrsid484402 New interest in illness stories. Friendship with Liz Stanley, who held a conference on Ken\rquote s book without telling him. Always tries to reply to letters. Letters from former students.

