bara connection from 1975. Close friendship with Harvey Molotch, who was then coming out as gay. Two children. Wife Linda killed in car accident. Ken went to America to visit him and from 1985-2004 taught a six eek summer school in Santa Barbara each year
. Harvey became a lifelong friend, now at New York City University. Beth Schneider and Peter Nardi are other American friends.
\par Misses teaching, but glad not to be marking.
\par Everard the most important person in his life. Support through illness. Kindness. No quarrels. He retired from Grammar School teaching at 50. Met at a Valentine\rquote 
s dance. By 1980 he moved in. Totally mutually dependent. Roles evolve. Everard more practical, and does garden, Ken does finances. Drinking \endash  co-dependency. But able to give it up totally, immediately.
